   MUST clearly display the official “Powered by HiCyou” badge on every publicly
   accessible page of the deployed application, service, or website that
   incorporates this Software.

2. Dofollow Link Requirement
   The attribution badge MUST contain an HTML hyperlink pointing to:

       https://hicyou.com/

   This link MUST be dofollow. Use of rel="nofollow", rel="noopener",
   rel="noreferrer", JavaScript-based redirects, or any mechanism intended to
   prevent link equity or crawler visibility is strictly prohibited.

3. Official Badge Usage
   Licensee MUST use one of the official badges provided by HiCyou:

       Light Mode: https://hicyou.com/badges/light.svg
       Dark Mode:  https://hicyou.com/badges/dark.svg

   The badge may be resized proportionally, but modifying its appearance,
   removing its text/logo, or replacing it with a custom badge is prohibited.

4. License Notice Requirement
   The complete text of this License MUST be included in any redistributed
   version of the Software. If the Software incorporates components of upstream
   open-source software (including MIT-licensed code), their original copyright
   and license notices MUST also be preserved.

5. Relicensing Restriction
   Licensee may NOT relicense the Software under any OSI-approved open-source
   license or describe the Software as MIT-licensed or open-source, due to the
   additional obligations imposed by this License.

6. Prohibited Actions
   The following actions are strictly prohibited:
   - Removing, hiding, or altering the required attribution badge.
   - Using nofollow or equivalent mechanisms to avoid link attribution.
   - Misrepresenting the licensing terms of this Software.
   - Attempting to circumvent any requirement in this License.

7. Termination
   Failure to comply with any provision of this License results in automatic and
